# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  A.P.E.X. .gitignore
#  Goal: never commit secrets, and skip generated/cache junk.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Secrets (NEVER commit) ---
# Ignore everything in secrets/ EXCEPT the example template and the keep-file.
secrets/*
!secrets/.gitkeep
!secrets/secrets.example.json

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/

# --- Personal health / profile data (NEVER commit) ---
# The live app keeps the profile + nutrition + health data in the browser's
# localStorage (on-device only), so there's normally nothing to commit. But if you
# ever export it or drop Apple Health files into the repo, keep them OUT of git.
health-imports/
apple-health-export/
export.zip
export.xml
*.healthexport.*
apex-profile-export*.json
apex-export-*.json
*.apexprofile.json

# --- OS / editor junk ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# --- Runtime logs (created on demand by the app; keep out of the repo) ---
# unanchored (**/) so this also covers python_backend_legacy/core_memory/logs/
**/core_memory/logs/*.jsonl
!**/core_memory/logs/.gitkeep

# --- Local AI config that may hold a private cloud-Ollama URL/token ---
# (ai_center.json is committed as a template; if you put private hosts in it, ignore it instead)

# --- Notes ---
# core_memory/ IS tracked on purpose (it's the editable memory store; example data only, no secrets).
# secrets/ is ignored above except the example template.
